translations: v．热情地亲吻（澳大利亚和新西兰俚语）
· They pashed each other at the party.
他们在派对上热情地亲吻了对方。

sentences.sentence: I made an appointment with him in an air-conditioned café and pashed my way though crowds of people I didn't know and who for some reason embarrassed me greatly.
sentences.translation: 我们约好在一家有空调的咖啡店见面。我挤过一大堆人群，这些人我不认识，但不知为什么，却让我很尴尬。
